      "role": "user",
      "content": "the manual counter idea makes sense. a lot of times these leaks aren't just a direct missing delete, but more of a slow creep where things get stuck in a buffer or a queue that never quite cleans itself up. it's hard to tell if it's a single logic error or just a bunch of small, tiny things that add up over time. do you have any specific tips for catching those kinds of \"sneaky\" or subtle leaks that don't show up in a single function call?",
      "source": "evaluator"
